s considering slow zone times, large mostly empty zones, and no sow equals 7 hrs.  Now bear in mind this is a good day, because you actually found a group at all.  That was old school EQ.  And no it was not fun. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=murel>Murel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1472<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/03 3:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ</span><hr size=1> I retired a long time ago...they got rid of the boats? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The two things that made the game big for me was the boat trips, and the Karanas. I remember one trip I made through Karana...ah screw it. Old timers' stories, and I started post-Velious so I'm not even old. <br>
<br>
Nowadays, from what I can read now and even what I could sense in the atmosphere when I finally stopped played nine months ago or so, is that the game doesn't start till 50. And I don't mean in some cheesy &quot;Life doesn't begin till 40!&quot; way, I mean if you are under 50 then as far as 90 percent of the player base (and the developers) are concerned, you're just a player-in-training or some such.<br>
<br>
All the changes they've made for the &quot;low-level&quot; game are bullhockey -- they've changed the game for the high level people starting low level characters. That's what all this don't-lose-your-body-till-10, getting-rid-of-the-boats business is all about. If they really cared about real low levels, they would have left that stuff the hell alone and made the game more interesting,  not streamlined it even more to get to the end even faster.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rombusmindspire>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Forum Tyrant<br><br>Owned by Ikeya<BR>Destroying EverWars...<BR><a href=mailto:rombus@graffe.com style=text-decoration: none><u>Contact Rombus</u></font></td></tr></table></span><br>  Posts: 7217<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/03 3:40 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ</span><hr size=1> It's Gryphon.  Oh, and if WoW follows in the footsteps of Diablo 2 it's going to suck beyond suck.  Thankfully though I highly doubt that will happen. <p><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.tritonguild.com/rombus/sig.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:Verdana;font-size:xx-small;">Officer of Triton, Member of Team Ice, Povar